    '-d[This parameter, if passed and non-zero, will cause bad blocks to sleep betwee…]'
    '-e[Specify a maximum number of bad blocks before aborting the test.]'
    '-f[Normally, badblocks will refuse to do a read/write or a non-destructive test …]'
    '-i[Read a list of already existing known bad blocks.]:input_file"'
    '-n[Use non-destructive read-write mode.]'
    '-o[Write the list of bad blocks to the specified file.]:output_file"'
    '-p[Repeat scanning the disk until there are no new blocks discovered in num_pass…]:num_passes"'
    '-s[Show the progress of the scan by writing out rough percentage completion of t…]'
    '-t[Specify a test pattern to be read (and written) to disk blocks.]:test_pattern"'
    '-v[Verbose mode.]'
    '-w[Use write-mode test.]'
    '-B[Use buffered I/O and do not use Direct I/O, even if it is available.]'
    '-l[option in e2fsck (8) or mke2fs (8).]'
    '-X[Internal flag only to be used by e2fsck (8) and mke2fs (8).]'
